{
  "texts": [
    "In-class practice serves as a springboard to self-study; students may further develop what they have started working on, ultimately submitting their material as part of summative assessment.",
    "The tutor participates as an equal partner in providing feedback during group discussion, but assumes a more active role in offering individual formative feedback behind the scenes.",
    "Students, for instance, upload work-in-progress pieces in an E-portfolio section of the VLE, which is where they receive individual feedback from the tutor.",
    "The module is assessed with two writing assignments.",
    "In the first, students can use one of the pieces they have started to work on during in-class practice, incorporating formative in-class group feedback, as well as E-portfolio feedback."
  ]
}